Before using a step, read the matching `reference/steps-{group-slug}.md` file for attributes, child elements, and examples. Group slugs use lowercase with hyphens (e.g. `Rest_Api` → `rest-api`).

## XML conventions

Always use these namespaces on the root `<testData>` element:

```xml
<testData xmlns:s="http://autox.yukthitech.com/steps"
          xmlns:wrap="http://xmlbeanparser.yukthitech.com/wrap"
          xmlns:f="http://autox.yukthitech.com/functions">
```

### Value specification (attributes, text, CDATA)

XmlBeanParser maps XML to Java beans. The same property can be set via **attribute**, **child text**, or **CDATA**:

- Prefer **attributes** for ids (`name`, `id`, `beanId`) and simple scalars/conditions.
- Prefer **child text** or **CDATA** for multi-line values or content with `<`, `&`, etc.
- Applies to test suites, test cases, steps, data providers, and external data files.

See `03-test-suite-xml.md` for details.

## Rules

- Every `<testCase>` must have a `name` attribute (no `#`), a `<description>`, and at least one step or validation.
- Use `s:` prefix for steps (e.g. `s:rest-invoke-post`, `s:ui-click`, `s:assert-equals`).
- Use `wrap:steps` and `wrap:validations` to group steps when helpful.
- Data provider iteration data: `${attr.{providerName}.field}`.
- Dynamic data provider external XML: `<dynamic-data-provider stepDataList="res:/data/..."/>`.
- Properties before `<clone>` are on `_this` when the bean loads. Use `prop: _this.field` in properties, or `json(jel=true)` with `@fmarker: _this.field` in beans.
- REST response body: `attr.response`; status code: `prop: attr.result.statusCode`.
- UI locators: `type:value` format (e.g. `id: button`, `xpath: //input[@name='fld']`).
- Custom prefixes: define `<custom-prefix-expression>` / `<custom-ui-locator>` in `test-suites/common/`; use with `c:` (e.g. `c:app: key`, `c:srchDropDown:vehicle`). See `06-expressions.md`.
- Prefer `<s:ui-fill-form>` to fill forms; use custom UI locator keys in form data JSON for non-standard widgets.
- End tests with at least one validation/assertion.
- UI suites should include `<cleanup><s:ui-quit-session/></cleanup>` at suite level.

